OL,3,CPPS to consider any basis for appeal
OL,4,Cagainst Oliver MacCormack sentence
OL,6,FThe Public Prosecution Service (PPS)
OL,7,Fis to consider whether there is any
OL,8,Flegal basis to appeal against the
OL,9,Fsentence handed down to a pensioner
OL,10,Fwho exploited vulnerable young women
OL,11,Fby supplying them with heroin in
OL,12,Fexchange for them working as
OL,13,Fprostitutes.
OL,15,FOliver James MacCormack, 71, was
OL,16,Fsentenced at Belfast Crown Court this
OL,17,Fweek, having previously pleaded guilty
OL,18,Fto 40 offences, including charges of
OL,19,Fhuman trafficking and controlling
OL,20,Fprostitution.
