OL,3,CPPS to consider any basis for appeal
OL,4,Cagainst Oliver MacCormack sentence
OL,6,FThe victims had vulnerabilities
OL,7,Fincluding drug addiction, homelessness
OL,8,Fand mental health issues.
OL,10,FMacCormack is the fourth man to be
OL,11,Fsentenced after a sexual exploitation
OL,12,Finvestigation conducted by the PSNI's
OL,13,Fmodern slavery and human trafficking
OL,14,Funit.
OL,16,FThe court heard the victims were
OL,17,Fheroin addicts and MacCormack would
OL,18,Fexploit their vulnerability to force
OL,19,Fthem into prostitution in exchange for
OL,20,Fhim supplying them with drugs.
